¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Definition} ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function is quasiconcave if its result on any point of a
    line segment is larger than its result on either of the
    endpoints. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssubsection{Notation} ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ is quasiconcave if $f(v) ≥
    \min\set{f(w), f(z)}$ for all $v$ on the line segment $[w,
    z]$. ⦉
⦉

